<h4>BufferBuddy Settings</h4>

<form class="form-horizontal" id="settings_plugin_buffer_buddy_form">
	<div class="control-group">
		<label class="control-label">
      {{ _('Enabled') }}
    </label>
		<div class="controls">
				<input type="checkbox" data-bind="checked: settings.plugins.buffer_buddy.enabled" title="If enabled, BufferBuddy will try to keep buffers full."/>
        <br />
        <small>If enabled, BufferBuddy will try to keep buffers full, otherwise it will monitor buffers only.</small>
		</div>
	</div>
  <div class="control-group">
		<label class="control-label">{{ _('Upload to SD Inflight Target') }}</label>
		<div class="controls">
			<input type="number" min="1" max="50" style="width: 4em" class="input-block-level" data-bind="value: settings.plugins.buffer_buddy.sd_inflight_target"></input>
      <br />
      <small>
        Specifies how many inflight commands to target when uploading to SD card. Increasing this will increase speed, however too high a value will cause buffer overrun issues.
        <br />
        If you want to improve SD streaming speed, increase `RX_BUFFER_SIZE` or `USART_RX_BUF_SIZE` depending on your printer.
      </small>
		</div>
	</div>
  <div class="control-group">
		<label class="control-label">{{ _('Stop buffering on command') }}</label>
		<div class="controls">
			<input type="text" class="input-block-level" data-bind="value: settings.plugins.buffer_buddy.stopcommand"></input>
      <br />
      <small>
        Buffer Buddy Will stop buffering and return to monitoring only when this command is sent to printer. Any Gcode command can be used.
        <br />
      </small>
		</div>
	</div>
  <div class="control-group">
		<label class="control-label">{{ _('Only start after x command was sent') }}</label>
		<div class="controls">
			<input type="number" min="1" max="35000" style="width: 8em" class="input-block-level" data-bind="value: settings.plugins.buffer_buddy.startafter"></input>
      <br />
      <small>
        Will wait to start buffering after this many commands was sent and received by the printer (Consider Ok enabled commands only) Max 35000. Set to 0 to disable.
        <br />
      </small>
		</div>
	</div>
  <div class="control-group">
		<label class="control-label">{{ _('Only start after x layer height') }}</label>
		<div class="controls">
			<input type="number" min="0" max="35000" style="width: 5em" class="input-block-level" data-bind="value: settings.plugins.buffer_buddy.startafterZ"></input>
      <br />
      <small>
        Will wait to start buffering only after this layer height Max 35000. Useful to keep small buffer on first layer for fast cancel. Set to zero to start right away.
        <br />
      </small>
		</div>
	</div>
</form>

